.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-tmux-install - Download, verify, and install a Citadel-managed tmux binary


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel tmux install [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Download a Citadel-managed static tmux build for this platform, verify its
SHA-256 checksum, and install it to the Citadel-managed path so persistent
terminal sessions work without a system tmux.

.PP
The downloaded artifact's checksum is always verified before install, and the
binary is never executed as part of verification.

.PP
Not every platform has a vetted static tmux artifact yet (macOS and Windows in
particular). On gated platforms this command reports that no artifact is
available; install tmux via your package manager instead (e.g. on macOS:
\&'brew install tmux').


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--force\fP[=false]
	Reinstall even if a managed tmux binary already exists

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for install


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-auto-update\fP[=false]
	Disable automatic update checks and installs for this run (or set CITADEL_NO_AUTO_UPDATE=1)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel-tmux(1)\fP
